Our
Drinks
Southwest Florida's premier oyster, and cold water seafood program. We pride ourselves on our hospitality driven service style. Also boasting an edgy craft cocktail program, thoughtful wine list, and forty four draft beer tap, round out the food and drink experience at Coldwater Oyster Market!

Thursday September 18th

Bring your friends and family by on Thanksgiving Day for a celebratory feast!

Fisherman's Stew
Semi private market room
Heirloom beets and fried goat cheese, salted almond vinaigrette,...
Caramelized scallops, truffled asparagus, smoked gouda risotto, burnt...
Interior, fully set rawbar table
Market tower
Baked Goat Cheese, with tomato, basil, bacon jam and crostini
Indoor/ Outdoor seating
Mamma mia oysters
The Nutty Paloma
Famous old fashioned
New england clam chowder
Pastrami sandwich
Funnel cake
Reviews
Review by Yelp
Dawn D.:
Great food and we loved the live entertainment! Best clam chowder I've ever tasted!  And don't even get me started on how fresh the oysters are!!!
Review by Yelp
Tommy M.:
Dropped in with a friend after running an errand. Not too busy nor noisy. Ordered fish and chips with a nice local stout that was on tap. Three nice pieces of cod lightly battered with seasoned fries and a small side of coleslaw...
Review by Yelp
kelly l.:
Absolutely outstanding food we enjoyed a dozen East Coast oysters which were absolutely fresh and delicious we also had for West Coast oysters which are very good although I prefer the East Coast...
Review by Yelp
Linda B.:
Delish! I had the beet salad and the presentation was wonderful plus it was so good. Then (because I am not a 'fishy' person) I had the Plain Jane smash burger...really good with little crispy edges! Husband had clam chowder that he said was very good and Maine lobster roll...
Review by Yelp
Matthew S.:
Amazing food and great employees. Have been there twice and not disappointed. The Dungeons crabs and tuna tar tar were amazing and the oysters fresh! Live music was pleasant and not overpowering. Open air space was also super nice! Highly recommend.
